 the bird image to a subfolder (images/bird.png) for this code to work.</p>\n<p>Otherwise, this code is a fairly simple update of the default hello.php (Hello Dolly) plugin that ships with every copy of WordPress.</p>\n<pre>\n&lt;?php\n/**\n * @package Put_A_Bird_On_It\n * @version 1.6\n */\n/*\nPlugin Name: Put a Bird On It\nPlugin URI: http://thisismyurl.com/\nDescription: Oh come on, how could I resist?\nAuthor: Christopher Ross\nVersion: 0.0.1\nAuthor URI: http://thisismyurl.com/\n*/\n\n// Echo the bird\nfunction put_a_bird_on_it() {\n	echo &#039;&lt;img id=&quot;put_a_bird_on_it&quot; src=&quot;&#039; . plugins_url( &#039;/images/bird.png&#039;, __FILE__ ) . &#039;&quot; alt=&quot;Put a Bird on It&quot; /&gt;&#039;;\n}\n\n// Now we set that function up to execute when the admin_notices action is called\nadd_action( &#039;admin_notices&#039;, &#039;put_a_bird_on_it&#039; );\n\n// We need some CSS to position the image\nfunction put_a_bird_on_it_css() {\n	// This makes sure that the positioning is also good for right-to-left languages\n	$x = is_rtl() ? &#039;left&#039; : &#039;right&#039;;\n\n	echo &quot;\n	&lt;style type=&#039;text/css&#039;&gt;\n	#put_a_bird_on_it {\n		float: $x;\n		padding-$x: 15px;\n		padding-top: 5px;\n		margin: 0;\n	}\n	&lt;/style&gt;\n	&quot;;\n}\nadd_action( &#039;admin_head&#039;, &#039;put_a_bird_on_it_css&#039; );\n</pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/byfVhPPEv67qdqEOUVZk8E237KI/0/da\"><img src=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/byfVhPPEv67qdqEOUVZk8E237KI/0/di\" border=\"0\" ismap=\"true\"></img></a><br/>\n<a href=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/byfVhPPEv67qdqEOUVZk8E237KI/1/da\"><img src=\"http://feedads.g.doubleclick.net/~a/byfVhPPEv67qdqEOUVZk8E237KI/1/di\" border=\"0\" ismap=\"true\"></img></a></p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data