11; does your site leave your users wondering how to get something they need? Perhaps their digital downloads? Maybe your site leave your users wondering how you came up with such a great design? Think about it&#8230;</p>\n<p><strong>The Lens of Curiosity Â </strong></p>\n<p>To use this lens, think about your user&#8217;s true motivations &#8211; not just the goals your site has set forth and making sales, but the reason the user wants to achieve those goas. Ask yourself these questions:</p>\n<p>- What questions does my site put into the user&#8217;s mind?</p>\n<p>- What am I doing to make them care about these questions?</p>\n<p>- What can I do to make them invent even more questions?</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/gamifying-wordpress-e-commerce-through-the-lens-of-curiosity/\">Gamifying WordPress e-Commerce through The Lens of Curiosity</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://getshopped.org\">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:104:\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/gamifying-wordpress-e-commerce-through-the-lens-of-curiosity/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"WP e-Commerce 3.8.10 beta\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 19 Feb 2013 20:53:40 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Developers\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"GetShopped News\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Plugins\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"WP e-Commerce Plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"http://getshopped.org/?p=302802\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:525:\"<p>We&#8217;re excited to announce that WP e-Commerce 3.8.10 beta is now ready for testing. This is the first whole release where our cycle is managed completely on GitHub. Our roadmap as well as development schedule were published on our GitHub wiki page, and reality turned out to be different from what we expected when we [...]</p><p>The post <a href=\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/\">WP e-Commerce 3.8.10 beta</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://getshopped.org\">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8:\"Gary Cao\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8599:\"<p>We&#8217;re excited to announce that WP e-Commerce 3.8.10 beta is now ready for testing.</p>\n<p>This is the first whole release where our cycle is <a href=\"https://github.com/wp-e-commerce/wp-e-commerce\">managed completely on GitHub</a>. Our <a href=\"https://github.com/wp-e-commerce/wp-e-commerce/wiki/Roadmap\">roadmap</a> as well as <a href=\"https://github.com/wp-e-commerce/wp-e-commerce/wiki/Development-Schedule\">development schedule</a> were published on our GitHub wiki page, and reality turned out to be different from what we expected when we wrote those documents.</p>\n<p>First of all, we received overwhelmingly positive feedback from the dev community, evident in the number of pull requests, bug reports and discussions. This whole release cycle has been 90% community driven and we&#8217;re very proud to have such support.</p>\n<p>Second, at the beginning of the cycle, we planned to have 2 major features, and 3 underlying architectural changes for this release, all within the span of 2 months. This turned out to be unrealistic. Even though we have many contributors, by the time we originally scheduled for beta (February 17th), we completed one feature, one architectural change, and a lot of bug fixes. So we&#8217;re faced with two choices: stick to the original dates and re-schedule the other tasks to the next release (3.8.11), or make amends to the schedule and delay the final release.</p>\n<p>Eventually, we decided to stick to the original schedule and follow <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/about/philosophy/#deadlines\">WordPress.org philosophy on deadlines</a>.</p>\n<style type=\"text/css\">\nblockquote#this {padding: 0 0 0 15px; margin: 20px 0 !important; border-left: 5px solid #cccccc; text-align:left; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; line-height: 26px; color: #444; width: 100%;}\nblockquote#this p {font-size: 16px !important; font-weight: normal !important; line-height: 26px !important; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif !important; color: #444 !important; margin-top:0 !important;}\n</style>\n<blockquote id=\"this\"><p><strong>Deadlines Are Not Arbitrary</strong><br />\nDeadlines are not arbitrary, theyâre a promise we make to ourselves and our users that helps us rein in the endless possibilities of things that could be a part of every release. We aspire to release three major versions a year because through trial and error weâve found that to be a good balance between getting cool stuff in each release and but not too much that we end up breaking more than we add.</p>\n<p>Good deadlines almost always make you trim something from a release. This is not a bad thing, itâs what theyâre supposed to do.</p></blockquote>\n<p>This might end up a small release, much smaller than 3.8.8 or 3.8.9, but we&#8217;re pretty sure you won&#8217;t be any less happy with it. Each of our upcoming release cycles will also be small and quick like this one. We figured by doing things this way, users get new features, improvement and bug fixes much faster and more frequently.</p>\n<p><strong>What&#8217;s new in 3.8.10-beta</strong></p>\n<p>We have completely revamped the UI for managing Coupons in the admin area. Below you can find several screenshots of this new UI and the full changelog.</p>\n\n<a class=\"thickbox\" rel=\"attached-to-302802\" href=\'http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/attachment/screen-shot-2013-02-19-at-11-09-36-pm/\' title=\'Main Coupon Screen\'><img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Screen-Shot-2013-02-19-at-11.09.36-PM-150x150.png\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail\" alt=\"Main Coupon Screen\" /></a>\n<a class=\"thickbox\" rel=\"attached-to-302802\" href=\'http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/attachment/screen-shot-2013-02-19-at-11-10-01-pm/\' title=\'New Coupon Screen\'><img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Screen-Shot-2013-02-19-at-11.10.01-PM-150x150.png\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail\" alt=\"New Coupon Screen\" /></a>\n<a class=\"thickbox\" rel=\"attached-to-302802\" href=\'http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/attachment/screen-shot-2013-02-19-at-11-10-34-pm/\' title=\'Edit Coupon Screen\'><img width=\"150\" height=\"150\" src=\"http://getshopped.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/Screen-Shot-2013-02-19-at-11.10.34-PM-150x150.png\" class=\"attachment-thumbnail\" alt=\"Edit Coupon Screen\" /></a>\n\n<pre>* New: Coupon UI is revamped.\n* New: [Shipwire] Addition of Shipping Services, Economy, Plus &amp; Premium.\n* Change: After filling out a registration form, the user is logged in.\n* Change: Limit quantity of individual products that can be added to the cart.\n  Default value is filterable.\n* Change: Remove FPDF which is not used any more.\n* Change: Return cart item messages as key =&gt; value array rather than HTML.\n* Change: Variation table class orderby to \'menu_order title\'\n* Change: When displaying packing slip, form data should be output in the same\n  order as that of checkout page.\n* Fix: \"you save\" prices are not correct on variations with a value over 1000\n* Fix: Cart widget missing closing &lt;/div&gt; tag.\n* Fix: Display the \"You save\" price as a currency, not just a raw unformatted\n  number\n* Fix: Ensure all variations are deleted when deleting a product.\n* Fix: Foreign characters are not displayed correctly in packing slip.\n* Fix: Improved performance with variations.\n* Fix: JavaScript error when no variations exist in admin.\n* Fix: Make sure Add / Edit Product page respects decimal and thousands\n  separators set in Settings-&gt;Store-&gt;General.\n* Fix: Manual / Test Payment instructions don\'t appear on transaction results\n  page and email.\n* Fix: Only print Google Analytics scripts on transaction results footer\n* Fix: PHP Warnings when bulk editing variations.\n* Fix: Prevent old paypal express from hijacking new paypal express callback.\n* Fix: Product category pages don\'t respect pagination and sort order settings.\n* Fix: Re-generate products pages\' IDs after plugin reactivation.\n* Fix: Refactor user account page\n* Fix: SQL IN error in wpsc_populate_also_bought_list().\n* Fix: Switching a purchase log status to \"Closed Order\" doesn\'t reduce stocks.\n* Fix: WPML compatibility\n* Fix: Wrong cache set for checkout form data.\n* Fix: split() deprecation notice in PHP 5.3+\n* Fix: stripslashes issues when duplicating products.</pre>\n<p><strong>How to download and test</strong></p>\n<p>Before you get too excited and rush to download 3.8.10-beta, please understand that <strong>this beta package is strictly for testing purposes</strong>. We&#8217;ve tested as much as we can and squashed as many bugs as we encounter. But we cannot be completely certain that it&#8217;s absolutely bug free, considering the vast combination of server configurations out there. That&#8217;s exactly the reason why we have beta releases, so that you can help us test and make sure that your site will work perfectly with the official release.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wp-e-commerce.3.8.10-beta.zip\">Â» Click here to download WP e-Commerce 3.8.10-beta here Â«</a></strong></p>\n<p>Then extract the downloaded package, and upload the resulting folder to your server&#8217;s <code>wp-content/plugins</code> directory, overwriting existing files.</p>\n<p><strong>I think I found a bug. What should I do?</strong></p>\n<p>First you need to determine whether it&#8217;s a security issue, or just a plain simple bug. Please read the following documents as it contains detailed instructions on how to report issues on our bug tracker. It only takes 5 minutes but would be extremely helpful!</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wp-e-commerce/wp-e-commerce/wiki/Reporting-a-security-issue\">Reporting a security issue</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wp-e-commerce/wp-e-commerce/wiki/Creating-issue-tickets\">Creating issue tickets</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Note to contributors</strong><br />\nWe&#8217;ll have a list of contributors to this release up when the 3.8.10 is officially released. We will use the name that you use for your commits (usually configured by <code>git config --global user.name</code>). We will also link to the website that you specify on your GitHub profile. If that&#8217;s not available, we&#8217;ll link to your GitHub profile instead. So take the time to prepare your GitHub profile!</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/\">WP e-Commerce 3.8.10 beta</a> appeared first on <a href=\"http://getshopped.org\">GetShopped.org</a>.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://getshopped.org/getshopped-news/wp-e-commerce-3-8-10-beta/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2:\"15\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s