ts as always.\nFor the time being &#8230; Have decided to continue to provide updates to Version 1.2 while still concurrently developing Version 1.3, which has been a big undertaking to bring some exciting features.  [...]\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:5988:\"<p><div id=\"attachment_736\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\" style=\"width: 310px\"><img src=\"http://www.viadat.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/10/horizon.jpg\" alt=\"On the Horizon ...\" title=\"horizon\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" class=\"size-full wp-image-736\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">On the Horizon ...</p></div>Still here working on great improvements for the Store Locator plugin.  Thank you all for your great suggestions and requests as always.</p>\n<p>For the time being &#8230; Have decided to continue to provide updates to Version 1.2 while still concurrently developing Version 1.3, which has been a big undertaking to bring some exciting features.  </p>\n<p>Additionally, to allow for quicker development, addons will be unavailable <em><strong>starting Friday, Oct. 30rd, 2009</strong></em> &#8212; this will allow improvements to the addon system, and 100% focus on development of new features (many of which we hope to be a surprise), since support is always provided for addons.  Themes will still be available however.</p>\n<p><strong>In the Meantime&#8230;</strong></p>\n<p>1) Continue submitting your suggestions &#8212; You can do so in the comment section</p>\n<p>2) More translations still needed &#8212; you can use this translation template to get started: <strong><a href=\"http://www.viadat.com/vdl/translation-template.1.2.40.zip\" >Translation Template &#8211; As of v1.2.41</a> </strong>.</p>\n<p>&#8230; to make translating easier, will most likely set up a dedicated page for translations, so that everyone can see who made the specific translations and also so people can collaborate.</p>\n<p><strong><a  href=\'http://www.viadat.com/store-locator/\'>Go to the Store Locator Download Page</a></strong>