ttle cleaner to allow for more logical management of the look and feel of your store locator map.<br />\n<div id=\"attachment_659\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a class=\"highslide img_1\" href=\"http://www.viadat.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/new_map_designer_page.gif\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this)\"><img src=\"http://www.viadat.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/new_map_designer_page-300x163.gif\" alt=\"New Map Designer Page\" title=\"new_map_designer_page\" width=\"300\" height=\"163\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-659\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">New Map Designer Page (Click to Enlarge)</p></div></p>\n<p><strong>Map Interface</strong><br />\nThe Map Interface now uses the new Zoom and Pan tools provided by Google, which gives your store locators a much sleeker appeal.<br />\n<div id=\"attachment_665\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 291px\"><img src=\"http://www.viadat.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/06/map_controls_update1.gif\" alt=\"Even maps deserve a makeover every now and then\" title=\"map_controls_update1\" width=\"281\" height=\"203\" class=\"size-full wp-image-665\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Even maps deserve a makeover every now and then</p></div></p>\n<p><strong>Version 1.3</strong><br />\nVersion 1.3 is already being worked on, and I must say, I&#8217;m liking the new features.  Plans are to have it ready no later then end of this month, June 2009.</p>\n<p><strong>Any desires, requests for features to be included?  Would love to hear them.</strong></p>\n<div id=\"crp_related\"><p>Â </p><p>Â </p><h2>Related Posts:</h2><ul><li style=\'padding-bottom:5px\'><a href=\"http://www.viadat.com/2009/10/great-things-on-the-horizon-continue-giving-suggestions/\" rel=\"bookmark\" class=\"crp_title\">Great Things on the Horizon + Continue Giving Suggestions</a></li><li style=\'padding-bottom:5px\'><a href=\"http://www.viadat.com/2009/08/store-locator-12283-is-required-for-wordpress-281-and-above/\" rel=\"bookma