('149', '9', '2011-03-07 21:12:36', '2011-03-07 21:12:36', '<a href=\"http://victoryblue.squareminc.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/images.jpg\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-101\" title=\"images\" src=\"http://victoryblue.squareminc.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/images.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"260\" height=\"172\" /></a>Diesel-powered vehicles continue to have a bright future in light of recent political, technological, and economical developments.Â  The reputation of diesel engines has shifted from being harmful to the environment to an appealing alternative for its fuel efficiency.\r\n\r\nNew technologies made this transition possible by significantly reducing the amount of emissions produced by diesel engines, a trend that is being reinforced by theÂ Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) in attempt to address the air quality challenges facing America today.', 'Environment', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '12-revision-5', '', '', '2011-03-07 21:12:36', '2011-03-07 21:12:36', '', '12', 'http://www.victorybluedef.com/2011/03/07/12-revision-5/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
('153', '4', '2011-05-24 17:02:05', '2011-05-24 17:02:05', 'Diesel Exhaust Fluid (DEF) producer VicNRG, maker of Victory Blue DEF, has begun production of DEF for Cummins Filtration at its plant in Fort Worth, Texas.\r\n\r\nJason Lower, Executive Vice President and Chief Operating Officer of VicNRG, told discoverDEF.com: \"We\'re very excited to work with Cummins.  Earning their trust and confidence by demonstrating our ability to produce the highest quality DEF available is justification for all the hard work and dedication of the Victory Team.\r\n\r\n\"The fact that Victory is trusted by OEMs is proof that the care and attention given to both our process and our service has paid off.  Victory excelled during the Production Part Approval Process (PPAP) evaluation conducted by Cummins.  There is no doubt that this success lends tremendous credibility to our operation.\"\r\n\r\nThe facility in Fort Worth has the capability to fill trucks, rail cars and to decant DEF into both totes and packaged products. VicNRG is constructing several other blending plants in strategic locations across the country, which will be announced on discoverDEF.com shortly.\r\n\r\nVicNRG\'s Victory Blue DEF brand is API registered.\r\n', 'VicNRG begins DEF production for Cummins', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '151-revision-2', '', '', '2011-05-24 17:02:05', '2011-05-24 17:02:05', '', '151', 'http://www.victorybluedef.com/2011/05/24/151-revision-2/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
