('307', '37', '2013-03-08 09:27:32', '2013-03-08 15:27:32', 'Stockton, CA, March 7, 2013â Victory Blue announces a new Diesel Exhaust Fluid (DEF) production/packaging facility in Stockton, CA. with the Grand Opening set for March 13, 2013.\nVictory Blue is now producing and distributing Victory Blue DEF from its new facility at the Port of Stockton. Victory produces and packages for companies that include Cummins and Valvoline.\n\nJason Lower, Executive VP at Victory said: \"This facility helps to solidify our distribution network on the West Coast. We are confident that our new Stockton California facility will provided a much needed supply solution to the region. The \"Victory Model\" has proven to be successful in regions across the country and we are certain that our drive to provide impeccable quality and service to our new customers in California will bring further success.  We are proud to bring jobs to the area and be a contributor to the ongoing efforts to improve air quality through cleaner emissions for future generations.\"\n\nVictory Blue\'s production facility in Stockton has 24/7 bulk loading, as well as a full inventory of totes, drums, jugs, and a line of equipment for the end user. Diesel Exhaust Fluid (DEF) is a new product required by many heavy-duty trucks, pickups, SUVs, Vans, agricultural, construction and forestry equipment delivered after January 2010. DEF is used to destroy harmful emissions in the exhaust and meet the EPA\'s latest strict environmental standards.\n\nDEF is non-hazardous and consists of 67.5% de-ionized water and 32.5% urea, and is used in combination with Selective Catalytic Reduction (SCR) technology. It is sprayed into the exhaust and combines with a catalyst to break down NOx (a harmful pollutant) into nitrogen and water.\n\nIn January 2010 emissions legislation came into force which requires diesel vehicles to significantly reduce harmful emissions of NOx and particulate matter. A good way to meet these standards is to use SCR and DEF.  Daimler, PACCAR, Volvo, Mack, Isuzu, Hino, Ford, GM, Navistar, AGCO, Case, John Deere, and others are using SCR,\n\nSCR technology offers many benefits, most importantly great fuel efficiency. On top of this, owners of SCR vehicles and equipment will enjoy greater reliability and a longer oil change interval, all of which adds up to impressive savings over the life of the vehicle.\n', 'Victory Blue announces a new Diesel Exhaust Fluid (DEF) production/packaging facility in Stockton, CA. with the Grand Opening set for March 13, 2013', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '306-revision', '', '', '2013-03-08 09:27:32', '2013-03-08 15:27:32', '', '306', 'http://www.govictoryblue.com/2013/03/08/306-revision/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
