('286', '37', '2013-01-29 14:25:28', '2013-01-29 20:25:28', '<h1>UPDATED: Victory Blue announces new Diesel Exhaust Fluid (DEF) packaging facility in Georgia and production plant in Texas</h1>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.govictoryblue.com/\">Victory Blue</a> is now producing and distributing Victory Blue DEF from its new facility in El Paso, TX, and has signed an agreement with <a href=\"http://www.govictoryblue.com\">Arcadia Interim</a> to package DEF in Thomaston, GA.\r\n\r\nJason Lower, Executive VP and COO at Victory said: \"This partnership [with Arcadia] helps to solidify our distribution network in the south-east United States. We are confident that strategic agreements with companies like Arcadia Interim will be vital to our expansion.\"\r\n\r\nVictory Blue\'s production facility in El Paso, TX, has 24/7 automated bulk loading, as well as a full inventory of totes, drums, jugs, and a line of pumps for the end user.\r\n\r\nDavid Crouch of Victory stated, \"As with all of our facilities, we are excited to now be able to say to our El Paso customers: \'It\'s on the dock and ready for you!\'\"\r\n\r\nThe packaging facility in Thomaston, Georgia, is the second of such agreements to have been signed by Victory Blue recently; the earlier expansion involvedÂ <a href=\"http://www.nelsonpackaging.co.uk/\">Nelson Packaging</a> in Ohio.\r\n\r\n</div>', 'News', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '91-revision-5', '', '', '2013-01-29 14:25:28', '2013-01-29 20:25:28', '', '91', 'http://www.govictoryblue.com/2013/01/29/91-revision-5/', '0', 'revision', '', '0'),
