('314', '37', '2013-05-23 11:57:12', '2013-05-23 16:57:12', 'Project will provide bulk loading 24/7 and packaging of API Certified Diesel Exhaust Fluid (DEF)\r\n\r\nPhoenix, AZ. â Victory Blue is proud to announce the opening of their new Diesel Exhaust Fluid blending and packaging facility. This facility adds a key component to Victoryâs highly efficient multimode supply chain.  In keeping with Victoryâs aggressive expansion in the DEF market, this facility is strategically located in a world class facility with the capability to distribute over 20 million gallons of DEF per year. This marks the 4th time in 2013 for Victory to announce a new facility opening. Victory is committed to providing the highest quality API certified  fluid and customer service in the industry. \r\n\r\nAbout DEF (Diesel Exhaust Fluid) â With the EPA mandate to reduce NOx emissions in diesel engines, SCR (Selective Catalytic Reduction) equipped engines have become the standard for eliminating the majority of Nitrogen Oxide (NOx) emissions. SCR systems use a solution of 32.5% Urea and 67.5% deionized water to treat the exhaust stream and reduce the NOx to simple nitrogen and water vapor out of the exhaust pipe.  This technology will also be used to reduce emissions in the Off Road, Agricultural, Marine, and Locomotive industries over the next several years. \r\n\r\nAbout Victory Blue, LLC- Victory, a Texas based company, produces Victory Blue DEF (Diesel Exhaust Fluid), an API certified fluid complying with ISO 22241 to reduce NOx emissions in SCR equipped diesel engines. Using ultrapure water and technical grade Urea, Victory Blue surpasses the industry standards for purity and quality.  Victory Blue has an international reach with production facilities coast to coast in North America.  (www.govictoryblue.com)\r\n', 'Victory Blue DEF now Open in Phoenix', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'victory-blue-def-now-open-in-phoenix', '', '', '2013-05-23 11:57:12', '2013-05-23 16:57:12', '', '0', 'http://www.govictoryblue.com/?p=314', '0', 'post', '', '0'),
